  \frac{\mathrm{d}x}{\mathrm{d}y}=-\frac{3}{5}\operatorname{cosec}\theta+\cot\theta = -\frac{3}{5}\sqrt{1+\cot^2\theta}+\cot\theta 
 \frac{\mathrm{d}\cot\theta}{\mathrm{d}y} = -\frac{1}{15-y}\frac{\mathrm{d}x}{\mathrm{d}y} -\frac{x}{(15-y)^2}=\frac{3}{5(15-y)}\sqrt{1+\cot^2\theta} 
