\dot y=5\sin\theta = \frac{5}{\sqrt{1+\cot^2\theta}} =  \frac{10}{\left(\frac{15}{15-y}\right)^{3/5}+ \left(\frac{15-y}{15}\right)^{3/5}} 
 T = \int_0^{15}\frac{\mathrm{dy}}{\dot y} =  \frac{1}{10}\int_0^{15} \left(\frac{15}{15-y}\right)^{3/5}+ \left(\frac{15-y}{15}\right)^{3/5} \mathrm{d}y = \frac{75}{16} 
